Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAPC presidential aspirant Boa Tinubu is focusing Niger in his ever-widening consultation as he prepares for the par’s presidential ticke in 2023.
Apart from visiting the state Gov. Sani Bello who endorsed him three days ago, Tinubu made a donation of N50 million to victims of banditry in the stae, and he just assured Sen. Sani Musa of good rewards for heling the APC in 2014.
Musa chairs the Senate Services Committee, and he’s also eyeing the party national chairmanship.
“The sacrifices of distinguished Senator Mohammed Sani Musa in 2014/2015 will not go in vain. The leadership of the ruling party is fully aware. Insha Allah, he will be rewarded,” Tinubu said. On visiting the senator in Abuja Saturday.
Niger is the first north-central state to openly endorse Tinubu for presidency.
